User Input: How do I request to change my vehicle?
Answer: To change your vehicle details, follow these steps: Go to your Lalamove Driver App Profile. Tap on Settings. Tap on Personal Information. Tap on Vehicle Details to change the vehicle information. Then click Change. Key in the 4-digit OTP code sent via SMS. Fill up the form accordingly. Upload all the necessary documents required. Update the reason of changing the information. This process will take 2 working days to be updated. You will receive a pop-up notification indicating if the request is successful or rejected. Reminders: For changes to Van or Lorry, you are required to go to our office after updating the app to get the sticker pasted. The changes will not take place if sticker is not pasted. There should be a sufficient wallet balance of $50 if you are changing from 2-wheels (this includes Walker or Motorcycle) to 4-wheels (Car, MPV, Van or Lorry). For 4-wheels to 2-wheels, the difference in deposit will be credited into your driver's wallet. For visual guidance, click here. Was this answer helpful?

When you arrived at the drop off point, tap on Arrive at the drop-off point, call the client to inform that you're already in the location. If the customer is not answering your call, you need to try to contact them via In App messaging. If you still have no response, then you can speak with one of my human friends. Please click here.
